<dl id="n10028c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10028c">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10028c"> 28(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> letterbox ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n10028c"><li>FW 472.19 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qC/lexqC.htm#n10028c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qC/l39qC.htm#n10028c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n10028c">MS BL 47482b-33</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:067 <a name="qA2d" href="../../FF/fdra/qda.htm#qC2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qC2d.htm#n10028c">Draft: III&sect;2C.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Aujourd&apos;hui qu&apos;il suffit de jeter dans <mark>une bo&icirc;te aux lettres</mark> une carte postale, un pli quelconque, affranchi ou non, pour &ecirc;tre certain que la missive s&apos;en ira rapidement et s&ucirc;rement &agrave; sa destination &hellip; <font color="green">[Today, it&apos;s enough to toss a postcard or any kind of envelope into a letter-box, stamped or not, and one is certain that the missive will go quickly and reliably to its destination. ]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n10055h" href="n10all.htm#n10055h">N10 (VI.B.16):055(h)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
